header.gameNote: COLLEGE OF CHARLESTON CLASSIC AT CHARLESTON SC

article.headline: IUPUI 67, Radford 64
article.story: CHARLESTON, S.C. (AP) -- Austin Montgomery scored 20 points and grabbed five rebounds to lead IUPUI to a 67-64 win against Radford in the consolation game of the College of Charleston Holiday Classic on Saturday. George Hill and David Barlow scored 16 and 11 points respectively for the Jaguars (6-7). Reggie McIntyre scored a game-high 24 points for Radford (5-10), including converting on all six of his free-throw attempts. Chris Oliver notched a double-double for the Highlanders with 18 points and 12 rebounds. IUPUI lost its first round game of the tournament to Fairleigh Dickinson, 61-58, and Radford lost its first round game to the College of Charleston, 68-46.
